properties.the facts: The capital of the state of Sinaloa became a major battle ground from 2008 after the Beltran Leyva cartel split from the Sinaloa Federation led by Chapo Guzman and continues to suffer intense violence
The recent sharp hike in the number of murders in the coastal city are usually  attributed to incursions by the Juarez cartel and the Zetas on this Chapo Guzman bastion

properties.the facts: The Gulf vs. Zetas battle to control this strategically placed Tamaulipas town began in early 2010 but went almost unreported until a particularly intense wave of shoot outs in November prompted a mass exodus of terrified local residents

The major border cities in the state of Tamaulipas were submerged in paramilitary-style warfare after long-festering tension between the Gulf cartel and their erstwhile enforcers the Zetas turned into open conflict from early 2010
